1
00:00:15,065 --> 00:00:16,745
- Mom, I want a balloon.
- No, no.

2
00:00:16,825 --> 00:00:19,305
- Please, Mom.
- It's Navya's birthday in two days,

3
00:00:19,385 --> 00:00:20,705
we'll get it then. Okay?

4
00:00:20,785 --> 00:00:22,385
- Okay. Promise?
- Yes, promise.

5
00:00:22,465 --> 00:00:23,425
Tomatoes for sale!

6
00:00:23,505 --> 00:00:26,225
- Hey, stop.
- Take some, madam. The tomatoes are good.

7
00:00:27,345 --> 00:00:29,425
- How much?
- Seventy rupees a kilo, madam.

8
00:00:29,505 --> 00:00:31,185
- What?
- Seventy rupees a kilo.

9
00:00:31,265 --> 00:00:32,425
Are they made of gold?

10
00:00:32,505 --> 00:00:34,105
- Madam, take some.
- Not at all.

11
00:00:34,185 --> 00:00:36,585
- I'll give you a discount. Madam!
- No, leave it.

12
00:00:38,345 --> 00:00:39,985
How much for the tomatoes?

13
00:00:40,065 --> 00:00:42,465
- Fifty rupees a kilo, madam.
- And onions and potatoes?

14
00:00:42,545 --> 00:00:45,585
Onion is 60 rupees a kilo
and potato is 55 rupees a kilo.

15
00:00:46,265 --> 00:00:48,545
Don't fleece me by calling me madam.
Tell a fair price.

16
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:50,945
Madam, I'm giving you the best price.

17
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:53,345
- Why would I fleece you?
- Okay.

18
00:00:54,065 --> 00:00:57,225
A kilo of onions, two kilo potatoes
and a kilo of tomatoes.

19
00:00:57,305 --> 00:00:58,825
- Okay, please pick the tomatoes.
- Yes.

20
00:00:58,905 --> 00:01:01,785
Baby, see? Red tomatoes. Only red. Okay?

21
00:01:01,865 --> 00:01:03,585
Come on, put the red ones in this.

22
00:01:11,665 --> 00:01:13,385
- Here you go.
- Your payment.

23
00:01:20,145 --> 00:01:21,585
This is not four kilos.

24
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:26,265
No way, madam?
I just weighed it in front of you.

25
00:01:27,705 --> 00:01:29,745
Give it to me. I will weigh it again.

26
00:01:37,865 --> 00:01:39,345
See for yourself.

27
00:01:44,985 --> 00:01:48,905
Listen, I can tell you that it's not
more than 3.5 kilos as I held the bags.

28
00:01:50,265 --> 00:01:54,545
Either you tell me the truth
or face the consequences.

29
00:01:56,665 --> 00:01:58,185
Shall I weigh it elsewhere?

30
00:02:00,825 --> 00:02:06,545
I tipped the scale by ten percent.
It was my mistake. I'm sorry.

31
00:02:06,625 --> 00:02:09,385
Replace the scales right now
and weigh it properly.

32
00:02:09,465 --> 00:02:10,305
Okay.

33
00:02:15,105 --> 00:02:17,465
- Good evening, sir.
- Good evening, Kamath.

34
00:02:17,545 --> 00:02:19,585
The new AC has revoked your suspension.

35
00:02:20,305 --> 00:02:21,865
<i>Come to the office immediately.</i>

36
00:02:22,985 --> 00:02:24,145
Sir.

37
00:02:34,825 --> 00:02:39,105
<i>This is my department's</i>
<i>human weighing scale, Mitali Kamath.</i>

38
00:02:44,065 --> 00:02:45,225
Harder. Come on.

39
00:02:46,745 --> 00:02:49,465
<i>She's also known</i>
<i>as the Google of our department.</i>

40
00:02:49,545 --> 00:02:51,705
<i>Customs officers are clueless</i>

41
00:02:51,785 --> 00:02:55,465
<i>about the value</i>
<i>of a lot of things in the world.</i>

42
00:02:55,545 --> 00:03:00,505
<i>But Mitali keeps track of the existence</i>
<i>of such exotic things and their value.</i>

43
00:03:00,585 --> 00:03:03,625
<i>This is her gift, and her passion too.</i>

44
00:03:04,345 --> 00:03:07,905
<i>She's a divorcee.</i>
<i>And she dotes on her daughter.</i>

45
00:04:30,705 --> 00:04:31,745
Kulveer Dhuria.

46
00:04:32,785 --> 00:04:34,865
Where from? Chhattisgarh?

47
00:04:41,305 --> 00:04:43,105
How long have you been working here?

48
00:04:43,705 --> 00:04:45,865
- Who are you, man, huh?
- Santa Claus.

49
00:04:47,065 --> 00:04:49,225
I've brought a gift for you,
just like Santa Claus.

50
00:04:55,985 --> 00:04:59,465
Don't waste your time
on those hippie foreigners.

51
00:05:00,465 --> 00:05:03,425
Let them go, you won't find a thing.
They are backpackers.

52
00:05:06,265 --> 00:05:08,385
This couple is also not hiding anything.

53
00:05:09,465 --> 00:05:11,865
They are bringing
some dead relative's ashes.

54
00:05:19,145 --> 00:05:20,665
Look straight ahead.

55
00:05:20,745 --> 00:05:23,185
Go and check that guy in the blue jacket.

56
00:05:23,825 --> 00:05:25,665
He surely has something to declare.

57
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:30,385
But why are you telling me all this?

58
00:05:30,945 --> 00:05:33,705
Because your face shows
that you haven't caught anyone to date.

59
00:05:43,465 --> 00:05:44,625
Excuse me, sir. Hi.

60
00:05:44,705 --> 00:05:46,025
Where are you coming from?

61
00:05:46,985 --> 00:05:48,545
- Bangkok.
- Bangkok?

62
00:05:48,625 --> 00:05:50,625
- Your passport, please.
- Sure.

63
00:05:56,385 --> 00:05:57,745
Thank you.

64
00:06:02,025 --> 00:06:04,705
Hey! What the hell is that?

65
00:06:06,385 --> 00:06:08,865
- Sir, these are marmosets.
- What?

66
00:06:08,945 --> 00:06:11,185
- Marmosets.
- Where did you get them from?

67
00:06:13,105 --> 00:06:15,465
- Got them from Thailand, but--
- From Thailand?

68
00:06:15,545 --> 00:06:16,945
Do you know they are illegal here?

69
00:06:17,025 --> 00:06:20,345
Turn off your cameras, guys.
Turn off your cameras.

70
00:06:20,425 --> 00:06:22,585
- Do you have permission for these?
- No, sir.

71
00:06:22,665 --> 00:06:24,385
Then how could you bring them in?

72
00:06:24,465 --> 00:06:26,265
Sir, they're pets for kids…

73
00:06:26,345 --> 00:06:28,225
Kids liked them,
so you brought them along?

74
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:29,785
Didn't you check our rules?

75
00:06:29,865 --> 00:06:31,905
<i>These are pygmy marmoset monkeys.</i>

76
00:06:31,985 --> 00:06:34,345
<i>It's illegal</i>
<i>to bring them into our country.</i>

77
00:06:34,425 --> 00:06:37,865
<i>But they are a trend among the rich kids.</i>

78
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:13,305
<i>This guy bought</i>
<i>two of these small monkeys at Bangkok,</i>

79
00:07:13,385 --> 00:07:18,305
<i>sedated them and put them in his</i>
<i>jacket pocket and brought them to India.</i>

80
00:07:22,465 --> 00:07:24,785
<i>The flight was delayed by a few hours,</i>

81
00:07:24,865 --> 00:07:27,505
<i>and the monkeys' sedation wore off.</i>

82
00:07:27,585 --> 00:07:30,825
<i>And as soon as they came to their senses,</i>

83
00:07:30,905 --> 00:07:34,865
<i>these little ones</i>
<i>started behaving like monkeys.</i>

84
00:07:34,945 --> 00:07:38,985
<i>How did Santa Claus get to know that this</i>
<i>guy was carrying monkeys in his pocket?</i>

85
00:07:39,065 --> 00:07:40,385
<i>God only knows.</i>

86
00:07:43,665 --> 00:07:48,745
<i>This guy calls himself Santa Claus,</i>
<i>actually his real name is Ravinder Gujjar.</i>

87
00:07:48,825 --> 00:07:51,465
<i>Gujjar is my best friend and batchmate.</i>

88
00:07:54,705 --> 00:07:55,545
Grandpa!

89
00:07:59,345 --> 00:08:03,425
<i>Gujjar's father, two of his brothers,</i>
<i>his sister and mother,</i>

90
00:08:03,505 --> 00:08:07,465
<i>his paternal uncle and his wife,</i>
<i>his dad's sister and her husband</i>

91
00:08:07,545 --> 00:08:10,865
<i>are employed in the Central Excise</i>
<i>or Income Tax department.</i>

92
00:08:31,865 --> 00:08:35,825
<i>If there was a competition</i>
<i>for the most corrupt family in India,</i>

93
00:08:35,905 --> 00:08:38,904
<i>Ravinder Gujjar's family</i>
<i>would've always won.</i>

94
00:08:45,264 --> 00:08:46,985
Come on, food is served. Come on.

95
00:09:02,665 --> 00:09:05,465
<i>Gujjar sort of hated this system</i>
<i>as he had grown up hearing their tales</i>

96
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:07,385
<i>of corruption since childhood.</i>

97
00:09:11,665 --> 00:09:16,385
<i>So, on the first day he joined Customs,</i>
<i>he had vowed</i>

98
00:09:16,465 --> 00:09:19,145
<i>not to accept bribe, not even a penny.</i>

99
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:21,065
<i>He hasn't broken that vow to date.</i>

100
00:09:24,785 --> 00:09:27,065
<i>He is hardly respected in the family.</i>

101
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,745
<i>And everybody considers him to be crazy.</i>

102
00:09:31,065 --> 00:09:33,145
<i>But Gujjar is not at all crazy.</i>

103
00:09:33,865 --> 00:09:36,425
<i>He is a soft-hearted romantic guy.</i>

104
00:09:36,945 --> 00:09:39,265
<i>Gujjar's love story is unique too.</i>

105
00:09:39,345 --> 00:09:41,225
<i>He had been working for just 15 days</i>

106
00:09:41,305 --> 00:09:45,025
<i>and he fell in love with the nice,</i>

107
00:09:45,105 --> 00:09:48,025
<i>homely-looking Meenakshi,</i>
<i>who worked at the duty-free shop.</i>

108
00:09:49,065 --> 00:09:51,585
<i>And Meenakshi liked Gujjar a lot too.</i>

109
00:10:03,865 --> 00:10:06,545
<i>They got into a routine</i>
<i>and two years passed by.</i>

110
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:09,265
<i>Gujjar got into AIU.</i>

111
00:10:09,345 --> 00:10:12,345
<i>Gujjar and Meenakshi</i>
<i>took breaks at the same time,</i>

112
00:10:12,425 --> 00:10:14,865
<i>and had tea from the runway canteen.</i>

113
00:10:17,425 --> 00:10:19,505
<i>At that time, Meenakshi wasn't aware</i>

114
00:10:19,585 --> 00:10:22,785
<i>that Gujjar used</i>
<i>to take her for tea outside</i>

115
00:10:22,865 --> 00:10:25,345
<i>because tea</i>
<i>was very expensive at the airport.</i>

116
00:10:27,665 --> 00:10:30,545
<i>Meenakshi's parents also loved Gujjar.</i>

117
00:10:30,625 --> 00:10:33,505
<i>As he made no mention of dowry</i>

118
00:10:33,585 --> 00:10:35,825
<i>and said that he'd do a court marriage.</i>

119
00:10:39,425 --> 00:10:42,425
Everything is finalized.
You guys just have to sign.

120
00:10:42,505 --> 00:10:45,785
I'll submit this, dates will be announced.
Then you'll get married in a jiffy.

121
00:10:45,865 --> 00:10:48,065
Thank you. Done. I'll be back.

122
00:10:51,305 --> 00:10:53,145
<i>It happened just last month.</i>

123
00:10:53,225 --> 00:10:58,185
<i>We were waiting for Meenakshi</i>
<i>and her family at the court…</i>

124
00:11:18,385 --> 00:11:20,825
<i>…but she did not come.</i>

125
00:11:20,905 --> 00:11:23,305
<i>Don't worry. No one died.</i>

126
00:11:23,385 --> 00:11:27,185
<i>It so happened</i>
<i>that the day Meenakshi realized</i>

127
00:11:27,265 --> 00:11:29,745
<i>that Gujjar was not trying to impress her</i>

128
00:11:29,825 --> 00:11:31,865
<i>with his honesty.</i>

129
00:11:31,945 --> 00:11:35,745
<i>He actually just wanted</i>
<i>to survive on his salary alone.</i>

130
00:11:35,825 --> 00:11:39,145
<i>That day marked</i>
<i>the end of Gujjar's love story.</i>

131
00:12:48,425 --> 00:12:51,225
Ravinder, your exile is over.

132
00:12:52,625 --> 00:12:55,825
Had I known that you were coming back too,
I'd have done a couple of more gigs.

133
00:12:55,905 --> 00:13:00,345
Good one.
Your sense of humor is still intact. Good.

134
00:13:31,305 --> 00:13:34,185
Fifty lakhs in here.
I found it under the washroom shelf.

135
00:13:35,025 --> 00:13:36,145
Put it in the seizure.

136
00:13:38,585 --> 00:13:40,785
Everything about you
looks very dicey to me.

137
00:13:41,745 --> 00:13:44,305
Is it just me
or have you called others too?

138
00:13:45,185 --> 00:13:46,545
Mitali and Ravinder.

139
00:13:47,345 --> 00:13:49,305
How will it happen without the trinity?

140
00:13:59,985 --> 00:14:03,105
Hey, Meena! Your suspension's over?

141
00:14:03,185 --> 00:14:04,945
I don't know, man. Let's see.

142
00:14:20,065 --> 00:14:22,585
Excuse me. Sir is ready for you.

143
00:14:34,825 --> 00:14:38,305
Let me have a chat with him
and then we can…

144
00:14:38,385 --> 00:14:39,385
Sir.

145
00:14:39,465 --> 00:14:41,985
Right. Carry on. Call me in the evening.

146
00:14:43,585 --> 00:14:45,945
- Hello.
- Arjun Meena reporting for duty, sir.

147
00:14:46,025 --> 00:14:47,385
I've heard a lot about you.

148
00:14:47,905 --> 00:14:50,425
- The most amazing things of course.
- Thank you, sir.

149
00:14:50,505 --> 00:14:52,265
By the way, we've also been told

150
00:14:52,345 --> 00:14:55,745
that a very young and dynamic officer
has joined the department.

151
00:14:56,945 --> 00:14:59,065
This is Mitali Kamath and Ravinder Gujjar.

152
00:14:59,145 --> 00:15:00,905
- Hello, sir.
- Hello, Mitali.

153
00:15:01,505 --> 00:15:02,625
- Hi.
- Hi, sir.

154
00:15:03,345 --> 00:15:04,865
My name is Prakash Kumar.

155
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:07,945
And I've been given the mandate
to end smuggling at this airport.

156
00:15:08,025 --> 00:15:10,465
But I cannot do that without you three.

157
00:15:11,105 --> 00:15:13,425
When I was chosen for this job,
I asked around

158
00:15:13,505 --> 00:15:15,825
and got to know about you three.

159
00:15:15,905 --> 00:15:19,985
And I was also told
the reason you guys were suspended.

160
00:15:22,145 --> 00:15:23,265
But welcome back.

161
00:15:24,025 --> 00:15:26,745
So long as I am here,
you needn't worry about anything.

162
00:15:27,385 --> 00:15:28,705
Catch whoever you want.

163
00:15:28,785 --> 00:15:33,305
But we've to ensure that smugglers forget
the Mumbai International Airport route.

164
00:15:34,665 --> 00:15:36,425
Do your duty without any tension.

165
00:15:36,505 --> 00:15:38,385
As long as you all
are playing by the book,

166
00:15:38,465 --> 00:15:41,385
I will be responsible
for anything that happens to you.

167
00:15:41,465 --> 00:15:42,625
- Understood?
- Sir.

168
00:15:42,705 --> 00:15:43,945
- Sir.
- Yes, sir.

169
00:15:44,025 --> 00:15:46,265
Our mission is
to destroy the Choudhary Syndicate,

170
00:15:46,345 --> 00:15:49,345
which brings
the maximum contraband to Mumbai.

171
00:15:49,425 --> 00:15:51,545
Based on intelligence from various sources

172
00:15:51,625 --> 00:15:53,065
I have compiled a report

173
00:15:53,145 --> 00:15:55,545
on the main players
of Choudhary Syndicate.

174
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:57,185
I want you all to have a look at it.

175
00:15:58,705 --> 00:16:03,105
Choudhary Syndicate operates from London,
Italy, Middle East, Ethiopia and Bangkok.

176
00:16:03,945 --> 00:16:07,465
The leader of
this entire Syndicate is Bada Choudhary,

177
00:16:07,545 --> 00:16:09,945
who uses his brain to run

178
00:16:10,025 --> 00:16:13,305
this entire syndicate
from Milan through his couriers.

179
00:16:13,385 --> 00:16:15,305
<i>Choudhary's back story</i>
<i>is quite interesting too.</i>

180
00:16:15,385 --> 00:16:18,145
{\an8}<i>It's a story of twin brothers.</i>

181
00:16:18,225 --> 00:16:20,785
{\an8}<i>Bada Choudhary and Chota Choudhary.</i>

182
00:16:20,865 --> 00:16:23,865
<i>Just as Vijay worked as a laborer</i>
<i>in</i> Deewaar <i>so Ravi could go to school.</i>

183
00:16:23,945 --> 00:16:28,065
<i>Similarly, Chota Choudhary ran</i>
<i>an illicit trade so as to educate Bada.</i>

184
00:16:28,145 --> 00:16:29,025
Betrayal?

185
00:16:31,985 --> 00:16:34,745
<i>Bada Choudhary worked hard in the hope</i>

186
00:16:34,825 --> 00:16:37,545
<i>that he'd study hard</i>
<i>and make the younger one quit his ways.</i>

187
00:16:38,465 --> 00:16:40,985
<i>But here, Chota's clout was growing.</i>

188
00:16:41,065 --> 00:16:44,385
<i>And big gangs</i>
<i>were reaching out to hook up with him.</i>

189
00:16:47,425 --> 00:16:49,705
<i>But he loved his freedom.</i>

190
00:16:49,785 --> 00:16:50,945
Join us.

191
00:16:51,025 --> 00:16:52,345
<i>And he didn't want to give it up.</i>

192
00:16:52,425 --> 00:16:53,265
{\an8}NO

193
00:16:54,025 --> 00:16:55,865
<i>But the story took a turn the day</i>

194
00:16:55,945 --> 00:16:57,945
- Yes.
<i>- Bada Choudhary became an engineer.</i>

195
00:17:00,265 --> 00:17:02,665
Pick it up. Hello?

196
00:17:03,945 --> 00:17:07,545
He's become an engineer.
My brother is an engineer.

197
00:17:07,625 --> 00:17:11,385
<i>Chota Choudhary was very happy.</i>
<i>And he was on his way home when…</i>

198
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:33,265
<i>That day Bada burnt all his degrees</i>
<i>in his brother's pyre.</i>

199
00:17:33,905 --> 00:17:37,305
<i>And he decided what</i>
<i>he wanted to do with his life.</i>

200
00:17:40,865 --> 00:17:42,745
<i>With Sharma </i>ji'<i>s help, he first</i>

201
00:17:42,825 --> 00:17:45,265
<i>killed all those who had murdered Chota.</i>

202
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:07,865
<i>And then, on Sharma </i>ji'<i>s advice,</i>
<i>he smuggled his first consignment.</i>

203
00:18:07,945 --> 00:18:09,225
<i>Back in 2003,</i>

204
00:18:09,305 --> 00:18:12,425
<i>mobile phones</i>
<i>were rapidly gaining ground in India.</i>

205
00:18:12,505 --> 00:18:15,185
<i>Thousands were smuggling mobile phones.</i>

206
00:18:15,265 --> 00:18:18,745
<i>But Bada Choudhary came up</i>
<i>with an idea to smuggle something unique.</i>

207
00:18:18,825 --> 00:18:19,945
<i>Memory cards.</i>

208
00:18:20,025 --> 00:18:23,305
<i>Smaller than two-inches,</i>
<i>thousands of memory cards</i>

209
00:18:23,385 --> 00:18:25,665
<i>could easily fit into a small box.</i>

210
00:18:25,745 --> 00:18:28,785
<i>Choudhary made 1.5 lakhs</i>
<i>with his very first consignment.</i>

211
00:18:28,865 --> 00:18:30,825
<i>Choudhary had found his niche.</i>

212
00:18:30,905 --> 00:18:32,745
<i>And that was smuggling.</i>

213
00:18:33,545 --> 00:18:37,185
<i>And he started bringing everything</i>
<i>from abroad that had a margin to Mumbai.</i>

214
00:18:38,345 --> 00:18:41,105
<i>As he was passing</i>
<i>through airports regularly, he understood</i>

215
00:18:41,185 --> 00:18:43,225
<i>that some customs officers</i>
<i>could be bribed.</i>

216
00:18:44,465 --> 00:18:47,105
<i>So he made deals with all of them.</i>

217
00:18:47,185 --> 00:18:49,145
<i>An organized payment structure was set up.</i>

218
00:18:49,225 --> 00:18:52,505
<i>And he began running his shady business</i>
<i>with complete integrity.</i>

219
00:18:52,585 --> 00:18:55,945
<i>His business kept growing,</i>
<i>and he needed more people.</i>

220
00:18:56,025 --> 00:18:59,425
This is Anna,
his nephew Rahul, and this is Suresh.

221
00:19:00,105 --> 00:19:02,665
They smuggle gold
from the Middle East into India.

222
00:19:02,745 --> 00:19:05,945
<i>Meetings with Anna</i>
<i>helped him understand the gold business.</i>

223
00:19:06,025 --> 00:19:08,465
<i>Anna became his top officer in Al Dirah.</i>

224
00:19:08,985 --> 00:19:10,945
And this is Carlos Junior.

225
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:13,305
{\an8}He sends drugs
from Ethiopia into our country.

226
00:19:13,945 --> 00:19:16,825
{\an8}<i>The responsibility</i>
<i>of collection and sale of stuff</i>

227
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:19,185
{\an8}<i>brought by the couriers</i>
<i>rests with Ramesh bhai.</i>

228
00:19:20,025 --> 00:19:23,585
This is Mrs. Syed, who handles
the operations in London and Italy.

229
00:19:23,665 --> 00:19:26,785
<i>She sends high-end bags</i>
<i>and luxury goods to India from there.</i>

230
00:19:26,865 --> 00:19:29,265
<i>Been in business for 20 years,</i>

231
00:19:29,345 --> 00:19:33,065
<i>Bada Choudhary's Syndicate</i>
<i>is India's biggest smuggling syndicate.</i>

232
00:19:34,905 --> 00:19:36,905
<i>At a photo shoot</i>
<i>for a fashion show in Milan,</i>

233
00:19:37,545 --> 00:19:39,665
<i>Choudhary's eyes fell on a swimwear model.</i>

234
00:19:39,745 --> 00:19:42,945
<i>He fell for her and that model converted.</i>

235
00:19:43,905 --> 00:19:48,265
<i>Bianca became a true Indian</i>
<i>and she got a new name, Binita Choudhary.</i>

236
00:19:51,025 --> 00:19:52,545
<i>They have a four-year-old son now.</i>

237
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:56,185
<i>And the happy family</i>
<i>lives comfortably in a villa on Lake Como.</i>

238
00:20:00,865 --> 00:20:03,745
Now, what I am going to tell you
stays inside this room.

239
00:20:04,665 --> 00:20:07,545
The three of you will work
for Central Intelligence Unit from today.

240
00:20:07,625 --> 00:20:09,465
Arjun, you will lead this op.

241
00:20:09,545 --> 00:20:12,465
To the outside world,
you are still the same.

242
00:20:12,545 --> 00:20:14,905
You'll continue to do what you were doing.

243
00:20:14,985 --> 00:20:18,585
There is no other way
to flush out corruption from the system.

244
00:20:19,105 --> 00:20:21,265
From today, our only goal will be

245
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:24,545
to eliminate the Choudhary Syndicate.

246
00:20:24,625 --> 00:20:28,905
Find smugglers, find corrupt officers
and let's do a thorough clean up.

247
00:20:29,985 --> 00:20:31,345
- Clear?
- Right, sir.

248
00:20:31,425 --> 00:20:34,825
Sir, we will need more people.

249
00:20:34,905 --> 00:20:36,065
Send me a list.

250
00:20:36,145 --> 00:20:37,865
Sir, may I ask a question?

251
00:20:40,385 --> 00:20:42,665
Hope you won't be transferred soon?

252
00:20:44,865 --> 00:20:47,985
No, I mean you brought us here and then--

253
00:20:48,065 --> 00:20:49,545
I'm here till the election results.

254
00:20:50,865 --> 00:20:51,985
I don't know after that.

255
00:20:53,145 --> 00:20:54,425
Good to know, sir.

256
00:20:55,825 --> 00:20:58,385
You just don't think, do you?
You just say what you want.

257
00:20:58,465 --> 00:21:01,425
Hey, what did I say? We need to know.

258
00:21:01,505 --> 00:21:03,825
He has put us on the hook,
hope he will stick with us.

259
00:21:03,905 --> 00:21:05,105
- It's simple, man.
- Just a sec.

260
00:21:10,505 --> 00:21:11,345
Hello.

261
00:21:15,345 --> 00:21:18,145
Don't create a scene here. I can explain.

262
00:21:18,225 --> 00:21:20,225
No, there's no need for that.

263
00:21:21,025 --> 00:21:22,785
I just came to give you this.

264
00:21:23,905 --> 00:21:25,545
That'll be 450 rupees.

265
00:21:25,625 --> 00:21:28,745
Two hundred for the sweets
and 250 for the garland.

266
00:21:30,705 --> 00:21:33,545
You've come to ask me for money?

267
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:36,625
Yes, why? That was my hard-earned money.

268
00:21:37,185 --> 00:21:39,465
I was going to spend it on our wedding.

269
00:21:39,545 --> 00:21:41,705
You don't want to marry me,
return my money.

270
00:21:42,385 --> 00:21:43,505
Hand it over.

271
00:21:49,745 --> 00:21:51,385
Neha, give me 500 bucks.

272
00:21:51,465 --> 00:21:53,225
Give me 500 bucks.

273
00:21:54,985 --> 00:21:56,505
- What happened?
- Just give me.

274
00:22:04,545 --> 00:22:06,345
- Oh, man.
- Keep the change.

275
00:22:07,385 --> 00:22:11,185
Hey, madam. I'm not a waiter
that I'll keep the change.

276
00:22:11,265 --> 00:22:12,865
I am a Customs Officer. Do you get it?

277
00:22:14,785 --> 00:22:16,065
"Keep the change."

278
00:22:16,145 --> 00:22:18,425
Meena, come here.

279
00:22:19,065 --> 00:22:21,065
Hey, come here, bro.

280
00:22:24,425 --> 00:22:25,985
Give her 50 bucks.

281
00:22:28,465 --> 00:22:30,585
- Gujjar…
- I need to pay her, bro. Come on.

282
00:22:35,745 --> 00:22:39,105
Wait a sec. She owes you gas money too.

283
00:22:42,185 --> 00:22:43,785
Fifty bucks for the gas.

284
00:22:46,905 --> 00:22:47,785
I'm so sorry.

285
00:23:32,865 --> 00:23:34,705
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

286
00:23:48,585 --> 00:23:50,705
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

287
00:23:50,785 --> 00:23:51,865
He's sitting outside.

288
00:24:04,825 --> 00:24:06,625
- Won't you try the--
- No!

289
00:24:06,705 --> 00:24:09,585
- Good morning, Ranjeet.
- Good morning, Sharma <i>ji.</i>

290
00:24:09,665 --> 00:24:11,225
- Come on, baby. Let's go.
- Come.

291
00:24:11,305 --> 00:24:13,185
Go! Go and play.

292
00:24:13,265 --> 00:24:14,865
- Good morning.
- Please come.

293
00:24:19,865 --> 00:24:23,705
Ranjeet, how come seven officers
got transferred in Mumbai in one go?

294
00:24:24,345 --> 00:24:25,625
Whose fault was it?

295
00:24:25,705 --> 00:24:27,665
It was due to Pawar's foolishness.

296
00:24:29,305 --> 00:24:30,545
He messed with the wrong guy.

297
00:24:33,225 --> 00:24:35,945
- And who is replacing them?
- We will get to know by evening.

298
00:24:37,265 --> 00:24:39,945
Don't worry. It happens sometimes.

299
00:24:40,025 --> 00:24:41,985
I don't know.

300
00:24:51,465 --> 00:24:53,705
I was thinking of getting
Gautam Jha into the team.

301
00:24:54,585 --> 00:24:56,785
Gautam has no interest in Operations.

302
00:24:56,865 --> 00:24:58,905
He has joined the Rewards team.

303
00:24:58,985 --> 00:25:01,145
He says, he'll stay there till he retires.

304
00:25:02,505 --> 00:25:05,065
- Where is Sajjad nowadays?
- Where else?

305
00:25:05,145 --> 00:25:07,305
Like a moth is drawn to a flame,
he'll turn up.

306
00:25:07,385 --> 00:25:09,785
Guys, we better explain clearly to him

307
00:25:09,865 --> 00:25:14,185
not to blackmail movie stars passing
through the airport. He clings to them.

308
00:25:14,265 --> 00:25:16,665
- Let's call Vincent.
- Yeah.

309
00:25:17,945 --> 00:25:20,665
- Contact Shreelata too.
- Yes. Lucknow airport.

310
00:25:21,705 --> 00:25:24,185
Bro, let's call Shreelata.
Should we call Awasthi?

311
00:25:25,665 --> 00:25:29,025
<i>As instructed by Prakash sir,</i>
<i>we started putting our team together.</i>

312
00:25:32,425 --> 00:25:36,945
<i>We called officers like Shreelata Nayyar,</i>
<i>Vincent Joy, Sajjad Sheikh, K.P. Awasthi</i>

313
00:25:37,025 --> 00:25:40,825
<i>from different corners</i>
<i>of India urgently to Mumbai.</i>

314
00:25:41,945 --> 00:25:45,185
<i>All these officers</i>
<i>had one thing in common.</i>

315
00:25:45,265 --> 00:25:49,345
<i>All of them were honest,</i>
<i>intelligent and incorruptible.</i>

316
00:26:03,505 --> 00:26:05,225
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

317
00:26:05,305 --> 00:26:06,625
- Sit down.
- Thank you, sir.

318
00:27:02,585 --> 00:27:06,705
<i>On our first day at work,</i>
<i>none of us had a clue</i>

319
00:27:06,785 --> 00:27:08,785
<i>that we'd have to pay such a big price</i>

320
00:27:08,865 --> 00:27:12,305
<i>for our honesty in the days to come.</i>

321
00:27:46,545 --> 00:27:47,545
Found anything?

322
00:27:56,545 --> 00:27:58,465
- What is it?
- Good morning, ma'am.

323
00:27:58,545 --> 00:28:00,785
Don't breathe down my neck. Move.

324
00:28:01,705 --> 00:28:04,465
Sorry, ma'am.
I was told to buddy up with you.

325
00:28:09,065 --> 00:28:13,385
What custom duty will you charge
a passenger who brings,

326
00:28:13,905 --> 00:28:15,905
and declares two cartons of cigarettes?

327
00:28:15,985 --> 00:28:17,905
Ma'am… Thirty, ma'am.

328
00:28:17,985 --> 00:28:19,265
Wrong answer.

329
00:28:19,985 --> 00:28:22,785
Awasthi, he needs to be trained.

330
00:28:24,065 --> 00:28:26,585
Come on. Sit down.

331
00:28:42,865 --> 00:28:44,665
- Stop this bag.
- Okay, ma'am.

332
00:28:45,465 --> 00:28:46,865
What's in there?

333
00:28:46,945 --> 00:28:50,345
Ma'am, there is shampoo, toiletries,

334
00:28:50,425 --> 00:28:52,465
chocolates, some toys,

335
00:28:52,545 --> 00:28:55,545
a mobile phone charger,
two watches and jewelry.

336
00:28:56,585 --> 00:28:58,465
But, ma'am, that's not gold, it's steel…

337
00:28:59,745 --> 00:29:01,425
Just a sec, ma'am.

338
00:29:03,425 --> 00:29:04,785
It's stainless steel, ma'am.

339
00:29:04,865 --> 00:29:06,585
- It's stainless steel?
- Yes, ma'am.

340
00:29:06,665 --> 00:29:09,425
- Shall we let it go?
- Yes. We can let it go.

341
00:29:11,385 --> 00:29:12,625
Come here.

342
00:29:14,185 --> 00:29:16,665
- Are these bags yours?
- Yeah.

343
00:29:17,305 --> 00:29:20,145
Grab your bags and come with me.
We need to check them.

344
00:29:20,785 --> 00:29:21,785
Sure.

345
00:29:21,865 --> 00:29:23,545
- Help her.
- Yes, ma'am.

346
00:29:33,585 --> 00:29:35,025
Ma'am, what are these?

347
00:29:35,705 --> 00:29:37,825
These are toys for my niece.

348
00:29:37,905 --> 00:29:41,865
- Such big ones?
- Teddy bears are usually big.

349
00:29:43,065 --> 00:29:44,385
That's true.

350
00:29:45,105 --> 00:29:47,585
But you see ma'am, this one is Chanel.

351
00:29:48,145 --> 00:29:50,945
It's worth a little more than 50 lakhs,

352
00:29:51,025 --> 00:29:52,865
and the Black Sense Market is little less.

353
00:29:53,665 --> 00:29:55,505
They're limited edition Bearbricks.

354
00:29:55,585 --> 00:29:58,625
So, it's up to you now.
You wanna pay the duty

355
00:29:58,705 --> 00:30:01,985
or shall I confiscate these
and take you to court?

356
00:30:02,065 --> 00:30:03,025
Choice is yours.

357
00:30:09,105 --> 00:30:12,025
I'll pay the duty.

358
00:30:13,145 --> 00:30:14,905
- Jyoti.
- Yes, madam?

359
00:30:14,985 --> 00:30:16,105
Take her with you.

360
00:30:16,185 --> 00:30:17,785
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

361
00:30:24,745 --> 00:30:25,585
Ma'am?

362
00:30:26,585 --> 00:30:28,585
These toys look so ordinary.

363
00:30:28,665 --> 00:30:31,465
How did you know
that they're high value commodities?

364
00:30:32,065 --> 00:30:35,945
Because internet wasn't made just for
TikTok, Reels and Instagram.

365
00:30:36,025 --> 00:30:40,305
Do me a favor. Go left from here
and count all the washrooms and tell me.

366
00:30:40,385 --> 00:30:43,065
- Okay, ma'am.
- Hello? Put that back.

367
00:30:58,305 --> 00:31:00,665
- Yes, tell me.
- Will you come to the APIS room?

368
00:31:18,865 --> 00:31:21,745
- Yes, tell me.
- Arjun, look at this passenger.

369
00:31:21,825 --> 00:31:25,185
She's done 12 trips from Al Dirah
to Mumbai in the last six months.

370
00:31:25,265 --> 00:31:27,025
And in the last three years…

371
00:31:27,825 --> 00:31:31,345
London, Paris, Al Dirah…
She's been everywhere.

372
00:31:32,625 --> 00:31:36,225
So? She might be from a wealthy family.
What made you doubt her?

373
00:31:36,985 --> 00:31:41,705
Forget the girl.
Look at her flight details.

374
00:31:41,785 --> 00:31:44,865
London, Kolkata, Mumbai.
Paris, Delhi, Mumbai.

375
00:31:44,945 --> 00:31:46,385
Al Dirah, Pune, Mumbai.

376
00:31:46,465 --> 00:31:50,145
From international to domestic
and then from that domestic to Mumbai.

377
00:31:50,945 --> 00:31:54,305
But the domestic destination
is different every time.

378
00:31:58,825 --> 00:32:01,825
<i>Priya Khubchandani's travel history</i>
<i>was quite interesting.</i>

379
00:32:03,465 --> 00:32:05,945
<i>There's a small loophole</i>
<i>in airlines operations.</i>

380
00:32:06,025 --> 00:32:08,585
<i>Many planes are used</i>
<i>for international flights.</i>

381
00:32:08,665 --> 00:32:11,705
<i>And then, the same planes fly domestic.</i>

382
00:32:11,785 --> 00:32:15,945
<i>For example, Sitara's flight</i>
<i>comes from Al Dirah to Lucknow.</i>

383
00:32:16,025 --> 00:32:19,545
<i>The smuggler's courier boards</i>
<i>the international flight with the gold.</i>

384
00:32:19,625 --> 00:32:23,345
<i>And hides it in the toilet.</i>

385
00:32:28,065 --> 00:32:31,625
<i>After landing at Lucknow,</i>
<i>the courier confidently exits the plane.</i>

386
00:32:36,425 --> 00:32:38,865
<i>The passengers disembark</i>
<i>and plane is cleaned.</i>

387
00:32:40,825 --> 00:32:44,945
<i>The new crew will come,</i>
<i>then the plane will head towards Mumbai,</i>

388
00:32:45,025 --> 00:32:49,225
<i>and a courier gets on to the plane</i>
<i>and grabs the gold at the right moment.</i>

389
00:32:49,305 --> 00:32:54,105
<i>Seat belt signs are now off. However</i>
<i>keep your seatbelts loosely fastened.</i>

390
00:32:54,185 --> 00:32:56,585
<i>You may now use the washroom.</i>

391
00:32:59,345 --> 00:33:03,065
<i>And exits the Mumbai domestic airport</i>
<i>without any checking.</i>

392
00:33:03,145 --> 00:33:05,185
<i>There's no chance of getting caught.</i>

393
00:33:05,265 --> 00:33:08,265
<i>Because who the hell will</i>
<i>smuggle goods on a domestic flight?</i>

394
00:33:10,145 --> 00:33:11,465
I'll look into it.

395
00:33:24,625 --> 00:33:26,265
<i>Gujjar's shrewd eyes</i>

396
00:33:26,345 --> 00:33:30,505
<i>had caught this passenger,</i>
<i>Priya Khubchandani's travel pattern.</i>

397
00:33:37,265 --> 00:33:38,985
Excuse me, ma'am. Mumbai Customs.

398
00:33:39,585 --> 00:33:43,345
- Where are you coming from?
- Al Dirah. Any problem, Officer?

399
00:33:44,025 --> 00:33:47,185
- Do you have your boarding pass?
- Wait a sec.

400
00:33:52,305 --> 00:33:55,745
One of my officers has noticed
your MO and travel pattern.

401
00:37:58,945 --> 00:38:03,945
Subtitle translation by: Monika Saraf
